---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Wine Education" description="Structured wine courses from beginner to advanced, including CMS exam preparation and blind tasting training.">
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <p class="text-amber-600 font-medium tracking-wider uppercase text-sm mb-3">Services</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-6">Wine Education</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-12 max-w-2xl">
      Structured learning for every stage of your wine journey — from "I know nothing" to "I'm sitting for the Advanced Sommelier exam."
    </p>

    <div class="prose prose-stone max-w-none">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900">Course Offerings</h2>

      <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-8">Wine Foundations (Beginner)</h3>
      <p>A 4-session course designed for anyone who enjoys wine but wants to understand it better. No prior knowledge required.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Session 1:</strong> How to Taste — the systematic approach to evaluating wine using sight, smell, and palate</li>
        <li><strong>Session 2:</strong> The Big Six Grapes — Cabernet Sauvignon, Merlot, Pinot Noir, Chardonnay, Sauvignon Blanc, and Riesling</li>
        <li><strong>Session 3:</strong> Old World vs. New World — understanding the philosophical and climatic differences that shape wine styles</li>
        <li><strong>Session 4:</strong> Wine and Food — practical pairing principles you can use every day</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Format:</strong> 4 × 90-minute sessions | 4–8 students | $600/person (includes all wines)</p>

      <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-8">Regional Deep Dives (Intermediate)</h3>
      <p>Single-session intensive workshops focused on one wine region. Each session includes 8–10 wines with maps, producer profiles, and tasting exercises.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Burgundy: Understanding Climat, Cru, and the Pinot Noir Spectrum</li>
        <li>Bordeaux: Left Bank, Right Bank, and the Art of the Blend</li>
        <li>Italy: Nebbiolo, Sangiovese, and the Diversity of the Boot</li>
        <li>California: Beyond Napa — Sonoma, Paso Robles, Santa Barbara, and the Central Coast</li>
        <li>Spain & Portugal: The Iberian Renaissance</li>
        <li>Sparkling Wine: Champagne, Crémant, Cava, Franciacorta, and Pét-Nat</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Format:</strong> 2.5-hour intensive | 4–10 students | $250/person (includes all wines)</p>

      <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-8">Blind Tasting Bootcamp (Advanced)</h3>
      <p>For serious students preparing for certification exams or simply wanting to push their palate to the limit. Modeled on the CMS deductive tasting format.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Weekly 2-hour sessions over 6 weeks</li>
        <li>6 wines per session, tasted blind with structured debrief</li>
        <li>Focus on grid discipline, varietal identification, and regional tells</li>
        <li>Includes classic and obscure varieties to build range</li>
        <li>Mock exam in the final session</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Format:</strong> 6 × 2-hour sessions | 3–6 students | $1,200/person (includes all wines)</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10">Private Tutoring</h2>
      <p>One-on-one sessions tailored to your specific goals — whether that's preparing for a sommelier exam, learning to navigate a wine list with confidence, or developing your palate for personal enjoyment. We work at your pace, on your schedule.</p>
      <p><strong>Rate:</strong> $150/hour (wines additional, sourced at cost)</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10">My Teaching Approach</h2>
      <p>I'm not interested in creating wine snobs. My goal is to give you frameworks — systematic ways of tasting, evaluating, and thinking about wine — that you can apply independently. Every session prioritizes hands-on tasting over lecture, and I encourage questions that challenge conventional wine wisdom.</p>

      <p>The best part? You don't need to remember every detail. You need to develop <em>taste memory</em> — the ability to recognize patterns across wines. That comes from deliberate, guided practice. That's what we do.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 bg-amber-50 rounded-xl p-8 text-center">
      <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Enroll or inquire</h3>
      <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Sessions run on a rolling basis. Reach out to discuss scheduling and group formation.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="bg-amber-600 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-amber-700 transition-colors inline-block">Contact Me</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
